In this paper we consider the following problem. Given a (<i>d</i> + 1)-claw free graph <i>G</i> = (<i>V, E, w</i>) where <i>w</i> : <i>V</i> → <b>R</b><inf>+</inf>, maximize <i>w</i>(<i>A</i>) where <i>A</i> is an independent set in <i>G</i>. Our focus is to minimize the approximation ratio (optimum/obtained) in polynomial time that does not depend on <i>d</i>. Our approach is to apply local improvements of size 2, using a "misdirected" criterion, <i>i.e.</i> <i>w</i><sup>α</sup>(<i>A</i>) rather than <i>w</i>(<i>A</i>). We find the optimal value of α for every <i>d</i>, and the resulting ratio is roughly 0.667<i>d</i> for <i>d</i> = 3, 0.651<i>d</i> for <i>d</i> = 4 and 0.646<i>d</i> for <i>d</i> > 4.